* Emacs Mode

** Emacs Mode Files

  To use the <<<ltc-mode>>>, you will need to copy the following files into a location that Emacs finds.  There are 2 alternatives of letting Emacs know where to find Emacs Lisp files:

  [[1]] Use a location that is already included in the <<<load-path>>>.  To view the <<<load-path>>> in your Emacs, execute the command <<<C-h v load-path>>>.  Then, download the <<<.el>>> files to one of those directories.

  [[2]] Add a directory that contains the downloaded <<<.el>>> files to the <<<load-path>>>.  Assuming you downloaded the files to a directory <<<~/LTC/emacs/>>>, add the following line to your <<<.emacs>>> or other Emacs configuration file:

---
(add-to-list 'load-path "~/LTC/emacs")
---
  You may want to confirm that the <<<load-path>>> indeed contains the new location using the command <<<C-h v load-path>>> after starting Emacs with the updated configuration file.

  []

  In order to enable the LTC mode in Emacs, add the following line to your <<<.emacs>>> or other Emacs configuration file:

---
(autoload 'ltc-mode "ltc-mode" "" t)
---

  We recommend to avoid adding a hook from <<<latex-mode>>> to <<<ltc-mode>>> as our mode requires the <<<latex-mode>>> to be fully executed before it works. The hooks are not guaranteed to be executed in particular order, so it is best to manually invoke LTC mode.

